The article is a letter from Senator Edward M. Kennedy to President Barack Obama. In the letter, Kennedy expresses his gratitude for the President's kindness and leadership. He commends Obama for his efforts in healthcare reform, stating that he believes Obama will be the President to finally sign it into law. Kennedy also discusses the struggles that lie ahead in achieving this goal but expresses his confidence in Obama's conviction and commitment. He concludes the letter by thanking Obama and standing with him for change and the betterment of America.